     NNNNAAAAMMMMEEEE
          docgen - generate a document source file from a script

     SSSSYYYYNNNNOOOOPPPPSSSSIIIISSSS
          ddddooooccccggggeeeennnn [ [ ----mmmm_n_a_m_e ] [ ----ffff _s_c_r_i_p_t ] ] [ -vvvv ] [ ----dddd ] [ _f_i_l_e ]

     DDDDEEEESSSSCCCCRRRRIIIIPPPPTTTTIIIIOOOONNNN
          _d_o_c_g_e_n generates a document source file by following
          instructions in the script file and interactively asking the
          user for text.  The script file contains a description of
          one or more types of documents in terms of the macros needed
          to produce the document.  The user may first be asked for
          the document type.  _d_o_c_g_e_n then follows the script for that
          document, asking the user to type the arguments for the
          macros.

          The ----mmmm option specifies a script for the corresponding macro
          package.  Scripts exist for the -_m_c_s cover sheet macros and
          for some types of documents for the -_m_m macro package.  If
          no script file is given, _d_o_c_g_e_n uses the script for the -_m_m
          macros.

          Alternatively, the ----ffff option can be used to designate a
          particular file containing a script.

          In verbose mode, invoked with the ----vvvv option, _d_o_c_g_e_n prints
          the macros and their arguments on the user's terminal as
          well as outputting them to the output file.

          The ----dddd option causes _d_o_c_g_e_n to print information about the
          script file as it reads it; this flag is useful for
          debugging scripts.

          If no output file is given, the output is appended to file
          "temp" (or file "temp.cover" with the ----mmmmccccssss option).

     EEEEXXXXAAAAMMMMPPPPLLLLEEEE
